The membership of the board shall consist of the following:
The commissioner of the Department for Behavioral Health, Developmental and Intellectual Disabilities, or the commissioner's designee;
The commissioner of the Department for Public Health, or the commissioner's designee;
The commissioner of the Department of Education, or the commissioner's designee;
The commissioner of the Department of Kentucky State Police, or the commissioner's designee;
The Kentucky state fire marshal, or the fire marshal's designee;
The executive director of the Division of Emergency Management, or the executive director's designee;
The Attorney General, or the Attorney General's designee;
One (1) representative of local community crisis response teams appointed by the Governor;
Four (4) members appointed by the Governor to represent mental health disciplines;
Two (2) members appointed by the Governor to represent emergency services disciplines;
One (1) member who is a mental health professional licensed for independent clinical practice, to be appointed by the Governor. The licensed mental health professional member shall serve as clinical director for the board;
One (1) member, appointed by the Governor, from a statewide chaplain's association involved in emergency services, who is trained in grief counseling and has experience in crisis response;
One (1) member from the Kentucky Chapter of the American Red Cross; and
The commissioner of the Department for Community Based Services or the commissioner's designee.
